<h2 class="post_list_item_title"><a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/worlds-great-stories-2/" title="View full">Winston Churchill Retells the World’s Great Stories, Part 2</a></h2>
<div class="post_list_meta_unit">
<div class="date-d">11</div>
<div class="date-m">Aug</div>
<div class="date-y">2023</div>
</div>
<div class="post_list_inner_content_unit post_list_inner_content_unit_left">
<div class="authorlooplist">By <span>RICHARD M. LANGWORTH</span></div>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/worlds-great-stories-2/" title="Read more about Winston Churchill Retells the World’s Great Stories, Part 2">
<div class="post_list_featured_image">
<img width="682" height="300" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2.0UCT2-682x300.jpg" class="lazy lazy-hidden img-responsive wp-post-image" alt decoding="async" loading="lazy" /><noscript><img width="682" height="300" src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2.0UCT2-682x300.jpg" class="img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /></noscript> </div>
</a>
<div class="post_list_item_excerpt">Churchill was busy in 1933, and Eddie Marsh wrote large tracts of the Great Stories. Yet Churchill signed off on every word and edited freely. His aim was not “great stories summarised, but great stories retold. It is essential to select the salient features of the tale and make them live in all their fullness.” These were old tales, but Churchill’s view was balanced: “Even in the 20th century, there have been some well-known writers, but I think that modesty must prevent me from pursuing that line of thought to its legitimate and inevitable conclusion.”</div>

<div class="post_list_cats">
<span class="post_list_cats_label">Posted in:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/">Explore</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/the-literary-churchill/">The Literary Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>

<div class="post_list_item_tags">
<span class="post_list_tags_label">Tags:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/alexandre-dumas/">Alexandre Dumas</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/eddie-marsh/">Eddie Marsh</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/harriet-beecher-stowe/">Harriet Beecher Stowe</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/lew-wallace/">Lew Wallace</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/richard-m-langworth/">Richard M. Langworth</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/wilkie-collins/">Wilkie Collins</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/winston-s-churchill/">Winston S. Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>
