<div class="post_list_content_unit">
<h2 class="post_list_item_title"><a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/worlds-great-stories/" title="View full">Winston Churchill Retells the World’s Great Stories, Part 1</a></h2>
<div class="post_list_meta_unit">
<div class="date-d">03</div>
<div class="date-m">Aug</div>
<div class="date-y">2023</div>
</div>
<div class="post_list_inner_content_unit post_list_inner_content_unit_left">
<div class="authorlooplist">By <span>RICHARD M. LANGWORTH</span></div>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/worlds-great-stories/" title="Read more about Winston Churchill Retells the World’s Great Stories, Part 1">
<div class="post_list_featured_image">
<img width="770" height="300" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ben-Hur-770x300.jpg" class="lazy lazy-hidden img-responsive wp-post-image" alt decoding="async" loading="lazy" /><noscript><img width="770" height="300" src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ben-Hur-770x300.jpg" class="img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /></noscript> </div>
</a>
<div class="post_list_item_excerpt">“[W]e are not writing great stories summarised, but great stories retold,” Churchill wrote Eddie Marsh. “It is essential to select the salient features of the tale and make them live in all their fullness, leaving the rest in darkness. Both Dickens and Dumas mixed up a lot of rot and padding in their writing for feuilleton purposes, all of which goes overboard through my lee scuppers.... I know A Tale of Two Cities well, though I suppose I shall have to re-read it. It certainly lends itself to dramatic pemmicanisation.” </div>

<div class="post_list_cats">
<span class="post_list_cats_label">Posted in:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/">Explore</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/the-literary-churchill/">The Literary Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>

<div class="post_list_item_tags">
<span class="post_list_tags_label">Tags:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/eddie-marsh/">Eddie Marsh</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/george-riddell/">George Riddell</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/richard-m-langworth/">Richard M. Langworth</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/winston-s-churchill/">Winston S. Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>
