<h2 class="post_list_item_title"><a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/kitchener-great-contemporaries/" title="View full">Churchill’s Descriptive Power: The River War and Herbert Kitchener</a></h2>
<div class="post_list_meta_unit">
<div class="date-d">13</div>
<div class="date-m">Jul</div>
<div class="date-y">2023</div>
</div>
<div class="post_list_inner_content_unit post_list_inner_content_unit_left">
<div class="authorlooplist">By <span>ALAN STRAUS-SCHOM</span></div>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/kitchener-great-contemporaries/" title="Read more about Churchill’s Descriptive Power: The River War and Herbert Kitchener">
<div class="post_list_featured_image">
<img width="770" height="300" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/1898Nile-770x300.jpg" class="lazy lazy-hidden img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="Kitchener" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /><noscript><img width="770" height="300" src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/1898Nile-770x300.jpg" class="img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="Kitchener" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /></noscript> </div>
</a>
<div class="post_list_item_excerpt">Churchill deftly describes Herbert Kitchener, Sirdar of the Anglo-Egyptian Army, with whom he would have more encounters in a greater war to come. No detail escapes his gaze. Kitchener inspected everything from machine shops to transport to cooking arrangements, even verifying the quality of grain, clothing, and food. Churchill at this time sees Kitchener as “ungracious”: cold and aloof, incapable of any human warmth. Later, in the First World War, he was more magnanimous.</div>

<div class="post_list_cats">
<span class="post_list_cats_label">Posted in:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/">Explore</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/great-contemporaries/">Great Contemporaries</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/the-literary-churchill/">The Literary Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>

<div class="post_list_item_tags">
<span class="post_list_tags_label">Tags:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/alan-straus-schom/">Alan Straus-Schom</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/herbert-kitchener/">Herbert Kitchener</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/the-river-war/">The River War</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/winston-s-churchill/">Winston S. Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>
