<h2 class="post_list_item_title"><a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/second-world-war-memoirs/" title="View full">“Trumpets from the Steep”: Churchill’s Second World War Memoirs</a></h2>
<div class="post_list_meta_unit">
<div class="date-d">24</div>
<div class="date-m">Feb</div>
<div class="date-y">2023</div>
</div>
<div class="post_list_inner_content_unit post_list_inner_content_unit_left">
<div class="authorlooplist">By <span>RICHARD M. LANGWORTH</span></div>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/second-world-war-memoirs/" title="Read more about “Trumpets from the Steep”: Churchill’s Second World War Memoirs">
<div class="post_list_featured_image">
<img width="770" height="300" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/BrFirstCB-770x300.jpg" class="lazy lazy-hidden img-responsive wp-post-image" alt decoding="async" loading="lazy" /><noscript><img width="770" height="300" src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/BrFirstCB-770x300.jpg" class="img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /></noscript> </div>
</a>
<div class="post_list_item_excerpt">Churchill had a right to make his case. He had attacked an allied fleet, fired generals, lost battleships, stalled on launching fronts, argued with Roosevelt and Stalin and carpet bombed Germany. He felt the need to defend his actions, knowing critics would gladly seize on and emphasize his mistakes. </div>

<div class="post_list_cats">
<span class="post_list_cats_label">Posted in:</span>
