<h2 class="post_list_item_title"><a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/king-george/" title="View full">Churchill and the Reign of King George V, Part 2: War and Peace</a></h2>
<div class="post_list_meta_unit">
<div class="date-d">19</div>
<div class="date-m">Dec</div>
<div class="date-y">2022</div>
</div>
<div class="post_list_inner_content_unit post_list_inner_content_unit_left">
<div class="authorlooplist">By <span>FRED GLUECKSTEIN</span></div>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/king-george/" title="Read more about Churchill and the Reign of King George V, Part 2: War and Peace">
<div class="post_list_featured_image">
<img width="770" height="300" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/1911Durbar-770x300.jpg" class="lazy lazy-hidden img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="The Delhi Durbar of 1911, with George V and Queen Mary on the dais. The last of three royal durbars, it was the only one attended by a reigning emperor. (Wikimedia Commons)" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /><noscript><img width="770" height="300" src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/1911Durbar-770x300.jpg" class="img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="The Delhi Durbar of 1911, with George V and Queen Mary on the dais. The last of three royal durbars, it was the only one attended by a reigning emperor. (Wikimedia Commons)" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /></noscript> </div>
</a>
<div class="post_list_item_excerpt">“King George’s reign has seen moral, social, political and scientific changes in the life of all countries and of all classes so decisive that we, borne along upon the still hurrying torrent, cannot even attempt to measure them. The means of locomotion, the art of flying, the position of women, the map of Europe, the aims and ideals of all nations—East and West, white and black, brown and yellow—have undergone a prodigious transformation.” —WSC</div>

