<div class="post_list_content_unit">
<h2 class="post_list_item_title"><a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/rhetoric-congress-1941/" title="View full">Rhetoric: How Churchill Scaffolded His First Speech to Congress</a></h2>
<div class="post_list_meta_unit">
<div class="date-d">19</div>
<div class="date-m">Aug</div>
<div class="date-y">2022</div>
</div>
<div class="post_list_inner_content_unit post_list_inner_content_unit_left">
<div class="authorlooplist">By <span>RICHARD COHEN & RICHARD M. LANGWORTH</span></div>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/rhetoric-congress-1941/" title="Read more about Rhetoric: How Churchill Scaffolded His First Speech to Congress">
<div class="post_list_featured_image">
<img width="616" height="300" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/1941Dec26HCP-616x300.jpg" class="lazy lazy-hidden img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="rhetoric" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /><noscript><img width="616" height="300" src="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/1941Dec26HCP-616x300.jpg" class="img-responsive wp-post-image" alt="rhetoric" decoding="async" loading="lazy" /></noscript> </div>
</a>
<div class="post_list_item_excerpt">“The orator is the embodiment of the passions of the multitude. Before he can inspire them with any emotion he must be swayed by it himself. When he would rouse their indignation his heart is filled with anger. Before he can move their tears his own must flow. To convince them he must himself believe.” —WSC, “The Scaffolding of Rhetoric,”1897</div>

<div class="post_list_cats">
<span class="post_list_cats_label">Posted in:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/churchill-in-wwii/">Churchill in WWII</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/">Explore</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/category/explore-articles/the-literary-churchill/">The Literary Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>

<div class="post_list_item_tags">
<span class="post_list_tags_label">Tags:</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/pearl-harbor/">Pearl Harbor</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/richard-cohen/">Richard Cohen</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/united-states/">United States</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/tag/winston-s-churchill/">Winston S. Churchill</a><span class="post_list_divider">,</span>
</div>
<div class="post_list_btn_more">
<a href="https://winstonchurchill.hillsdale.edu/rhetoric-congress-1941/" class="btn btn-default" title="Read more" aria-label="Read more about Rhetoric: How Churchill Scaffolded His First Speech to Congress">Read more</a>
